Mask and SEGS nodes are provided to account for preference. I'm not really sure what the difference is!

The original intention was to have a switch here to flip between Mask and SEGS detailing, but I couldn't get it to work. To pick between them, simply bypass the one you aren't using, and route the "image" *output* widget of the one you *are* using to the top reroute (the blue card-shaped one.)

You may want to do multiple passes for different targets for whatever reason. To do so, just copy this group, route the Basic Pipe widget from whichever Detailer Pipe node is currently active to the one you'll be using next. You can use the other two Reroutes are provided for convenience; Mask on top (purple), SEGS on bottom (cyan.)

As long as Florence+SAM2 can agree on where it is, you can use *anything* for your prompt. Get creative! Multiple targets can be specified with commas.

sam2_hiera_large isn't always the best! You might try the others.
SAM2's masks are sometimes a bit small, causing seams on the detailed area, so we dilate the mask to account for it. Tweak this value to taste.
